-- French Stocks: ArcelorMittal, Technip Shares Move in Paris
-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 2010-11-01T17:08:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/cac-40-index-advances-arcelormittal-technip-total-lead-gains-in-paris.html
France’s  CAC 40 Index  gained 0.2
percent to 3,841.11 at the 5.30 p.m. close in Paris, as Chinese
manufacturing expanded at the fastest pace in six months and a
gauge of U.S. manufacturing unexpectedly gained, bolstering
confidence in the global economic recovery.  The SBF 120 Index 
climbed 0.3 percent to 2,866.05 today.  The following shares rose or fell in Paris. Stock symbols
are in parentheses.  ArcelorMittal  (MT NA), the world’s biggest steelmaker,
surged 1.8 percent to 23.52 euros as copper, lead, nickel, tin
and zinc all rose on the London Metal Exchange.  Separately, the company agreed to supply the Czech unit of
Russia’s Evraz Group SA with pig iron, Evraz said in a statement
today.  Technip SA  (TEC FP), Europe’s second-largest oilfield-
services provider, climbed 4 percent to 62.78 euros, the biggest
gain in three months. Crude oil for December delivery rose
$1.82, or 2.2 percent, to $83.25 a barrel at 11:58 a.m. on the
New York Mercantile Exchange. Futures touched $83.86, the
highest level since Oct. 4. Prices are up 8.1 percent from a
year ago.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Julie Cruz  in Frankfurt at 
 jcruz6@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at   dmerritt1@bloomberg.net . 